OL,3,CDonald Trump tells BBC to apologise by
OL,4,CFriday or face billion-dollar lawsuit
OL,6,FBBC chairman Samir Shah has apologised
OL,7,Ffor an "error of judgment" and two of
OL,8,Fthe corporation's most senior figures
OL,9,F` chief executive of BBC News Deborah
OL,10,FTurness and director-general Tim Davie
OL,11,F` resigned from their positions on
OL,12,FSunday.
OL,14,FThe Prescott memo raised concerns
OL,15,Fabout the way clips of Mr Trump's
OL,16,Fspeech were spliced together to make
OL,17,Fit appear he had told supporters he
OL,18,Fwas going to walk to the US Capitol
OL,19,Fwith them to "fight like hell".
